{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01XSoFHjw57dwtsqDPdZyC2V","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"TLS is now enabled on the MongoDB replica set. Done.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Certificates** — generated in the `openssl-toolbox` pod with `openssl`:\n- A self-signed **CA** (`ca.crt`)\n- A **server** cert/key bundled as `server.pem`, with SANs covering all replica-set DNS names (`mongo-rs-{0,1,2}.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`, the `mongo` service, `localhost`/`127.0.0.1`)\n- A **client** cert/key bundled as `client.pem`\n\n**Delivery** — bundled the three files into a Kubernetes Secret `mongo-tls` and mounted it read-only at `/etc/tls` in the `mongo-rs` StatefulSet pods.\n\n**TLS enablement** — patched the StatefulSet's `mongod` command (strategic-merge, after a first attempt with a JSON merge patch wrongly dropped the `image` field) to add:\n```\n--tlsMode requireTLS\n--tlsCertificateKeyFile /etc/tls/server.pem\n--tlsCAFile /etc/tls/ca.crt\n```\nThe rolling update recreated all 3 pods; the replica set reconverged with one PRIMARY and two SECONDARYs over TLS.\n\n**Verification**\n- Files `ca.crt`, `server.pem`, `client.pem` present at `/etc/tls` in all three pods.\n- **Plain (non-TLS) connection fails** — `mongosh` without `--tls` gets the connection closed.\n- **TLS connection succeeds** — `mongosh --tls --tlsCAFile /etc/tls/ca.crt --tlsCertificateKeyFile /etc/tls/client.pem` pings `ok:1` and reports a healthy replica set."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":775,"cache_read_input_tokens":39466,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":775},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b6eb6894-d3f5-4c42-bd53-585f1671ad39","uuid":"78ab5cd5-53ca-47e2-9a04-ca184cba5b09","request_i